ENROLLMENT OPEN THROUGH FRIDAY 5/28

For those of you who missed out on our sold-out inaugural Certification Course, now’s your chance to get on the path to becoming a Certified Ganjier https://www.ganjier.com/first-step/

When our first Ganjier course sold out in two weeks, we realized the need for an option that provided greater access with more financial and scheduling flexibility.

Now you can take "The First Step" in becoming a Certified Ganjier, including:
 
✅Full access to the Ganjier Online Training Course materials.
✅Full access to the exclusive Ganjier Systematic Assessment Protocol (the SAP App).
✅First-in-line priority enrollment access to our expert-led live training sessions and Certification exams before they open to the public.

If you’re ready to join the most rigorous and comprehensive training for understanding cannabis quality, properly assessing cannabis flower and concentrates, providing the highest level of service to customers, and truly appreciating the nuances, complexities and benefits cannabis has to offer, your Ganjier journey awaits.

Find all the details and enroll now at https://www.ganjier.com/first-step/

node.text:
Full video! What an exciting day at Ganja Ma Gardens! The team was doing Gender ID Testing all day - delicately snipping bits off of leaves from each start and gently placing them onto the "plates" which will get mailed to LeafWorks. There they will be able to test them for their gender, saving us so much time, water, soil, effort, and money - plus the girl plants will be planted in their final holes that much earlier.

Check out the video of the process being explained by our head gardener, Chris Larsen-Gould (@perfect_compost), and Swami too.  I think you'll be convinced of how effective this is. Thanks, Leafworks!

Two years in the works with some of our most respected colleagues —Welcome to #theganjier
(Reposted from @the_ganjier)

—

Swami Chaitanya is a familiar face in the cannabis industry, as he is the founder of the renowned sun-grown / moon-harvested cannabis brand Swami Select, he’s a perennial judge at The Emerald Cup; one of the cannabis industry’s most prestigious competitions, and he is a sought after educator on the virtues of sun-grown organic cannabis. 

Now he is your instructor in Ganjier, teaching you Cannabis History, Art and Science of Cannabis Cultivation, and Assessing Cannabis Flowers.

Join the interest list at www.Ganjier.com 

#Ganjier #CannabisSommelier #SwamiSelect 
@swamiselect

node.text:
The memorial gathering in honor of our beloved Frenchy Cannoli was perfectly sublime and inspiring. Thanks to Doc Greens for offering such a perfect venue and to all the crew who managed to get it sent around the globe via the internet.

Madame Cannoli (aka Kimberly) arranged for every one of the 31 friends and family present to really feel Frenchy and his spirit, through words, psychedelic trance music and prayers… and lots of hashish!

As she said at one point, "Let's hotbox the heavens for Frenchy!"

It was our honor to offer Hindu rituals and create an altar with Frenchy photos, Ganja Ma (goddess of cannabis), the Buddha (Frenchy was a devotee of Tibetan Buddhism) and amonnorah in honor the Jewish traditions.

We heard from friends around the world - from Mila in Amsterdam, Josh and Kelly of DEM Pure in Canada, the Israeli connigent who recited the Kaddish, and so many more. Several very close friends and family of Frenchy also offered words and memories, and yes, the tears were flowing.

We all love this man so very much and will miss him more than we can express, but this was a perfect way to celebrate him and feel his spirit, and hear his laughter, always in our hearts.

Our endless love goes out to his wife Kimbertly and daughter Oceane - they will carry on his legacy with grace and wisdom.

Meanwhile our farmers are evacuated along with Tipu, but we ask for your prayers please. Love to all and may all our neighbors be safe ❤️

node.text:
It's never easy to leave the ranch, but for such a fun event as we had yesterday it's totally worth it!

We started out with our friends at @reddoorremedies in #Cloverdale where they hosted an outside meet-and-greet on a lovely warm day with blue skies and wonderful people, including three of our favorite cannabis women, @gaynellelizabeth - @cajammie - and @sensimagazine.norcal 💚

Oh, and another amazing lady cannabis friend: Gigi the Pig who came with her mom and dad Holly and Mike of @mr.ganjagold Tarantula pre-rolls.

Several of us then rolled over to the #CloverdalePlaza afterwards for a dance under the stars with incredible music from #RoyRogers and #TheDeltaRhythmKings - that man can make his guitar sing the blues and more! 

Good friends and great music - what more can you ask for? Oh, some fantastic cannabis too!

Be sure to step into #RedDoorRemedies anytime you are in or near Cloverdale 🌞🌙✨💛

We hope to see you there!

From @Madame_Cannoli, Kimberly -

I'd like to invite you to join us in a little virtual celebration of Frenchy's life Sunday, August 15th. The virtual ceremony will start at 11:30 am California time. The Livestream will be from both @FrenchyCannoli IG & FB accounts. 🙏
⁠
Frenchy was spiritual but not religious. That said, for my comfort, meaning, and joy I've asked friends from three different spiritual orientations - Hindu, Jewish, and Buddhist - to share a blessing from their traditions with us during this celebration of Frenchy's life. And, of course, I've included a celebration of Frenchy's beloved hashish as part of the ceremony. ⁠
⁠
Tentative Schedule⁠

11 am welcome guests (Livestream to start at 11:30)⁠
11:30 blessing ceremony from Swami & Nikki⁠
11:45 shared memories from friends⁠
Noon Jewish blessing from Frenchy's friends⁠
12:30 Group smoke around the world in Frenchy's honor lead by his friends @lakalada in Barcelona⁠
1 pm shared memories from friends⁠
1:30 Teyata Om Bekanze Buddhist chant ⁠

Mellow trance music to wrap up the celebration⁠
⁠
Looking forward to creating a lot of hashish smoke with you to celebrate our beloved Frenchy on August 15th. 🙏

__________

Please join the celebration via the Live Stream and please share this info with your friends 💚🌞

node.text:
It's so wonderful to see a project we have worked on for so long come to fruition, and that's just what it was like the past two days at the (@the_ganjier ) #Ganjier Certification Live Training.

We ventured across the County line into southern #Humboldt to the @cookies_onelog where we met with 13 students and and other council members/teachers such as Aaron Varney, Patrick King, Kevin Jodrey, Nick Tanem aka NikkaT, Wendy Kornberg and Derek Gilman, the devoted Director of the program.

Activities included learning how to deeply assess cannabis from looks and aroma to taste and effects - with lots of smoking as a study tool - and a fascinating visit to Wendy Kornberg's cannabis farm.

What joy to see the student faces light up at the fresh experiences. Now they will study up for their final exam before getting fully certificated and ready to take the knowledge out into the world.

What a great program - and we are honored to be a part of it! 🌞🌙✨

Ahhh it felt so great to return to visit our friends in Soquel at @thcsoquel last Friday. 

We hadn’t been there since before the craziness of last year and many #SwamiSelect flower fans came to greet us - including Nikki’s sister Carla and brother-in-law Patrick.

The staff at THC is among the best you’ll ever experience… friendly, very knowledgeable, and just a great no-pressure vibe the entire time you are in the shop. A breath of fresh air every time!

Cannabis is the great connector of friends and family 🌞🌙✨💛
